<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 9:42PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Armstrong
County through 1015 PM CDT...
At 942 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Palo Duro Canyon, or 13 miles southwest of Claude,
moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Claude and Washburn.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
